Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.28,0:00:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to another edition \Nof JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt discouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.39,0:00:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,due to circumstances beyond your control? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.06,0:00:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll discuss how we can still have joy \Ndespite our limitations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.00,0:00:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll see examples, \Nboth Biblical and modern day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that will encourage us \Nto keep giving Jehovah our best.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.64,0:00:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah had faced several reasons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.48,0:00:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to become discouraged and give up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.91,0:00:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah help him carry on \Nwith courage and faith? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And what lessons from his experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.35,0:00:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,can we apply to problems we face today?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.96,0:00:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we change \Nour personality for the better? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.66,0:00:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can with Jehovah’s spirit \Nand diligent effort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This brother describes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,how far his personality and lifestyle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,took him away from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.97,0:01:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He explains how he regained \Na clean conscience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.48,0:01:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and freeness of speech.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.95,0:01:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can turn tragic events \Ncaused by man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.82,0:01:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,into open doors of activity \Nfor His loyal Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.89,0:01:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In this report from Greece, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.79,0:01:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll learn how our brothers \Nare bringing spiritual comfort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to refugees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.53,0:01:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re watching the June 2017 edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.93,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.92,0:01:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many exciting things happening\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.89,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, month after month, we read articles,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,watch videos, and hear personal experiences\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.93,0:01:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,about our brothers and sisters \Nwho are doing more for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They are serving where \Nthe need is greater or reaching out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.97,0:02:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for the School for Kingdom Evangelizers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.58,0:02:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They are working \Non construction, renovation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,maintenance of Kingdom Halls, \Nor other theocratic projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.95,0:02:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt, \Nmany of you watching this program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are excitedly looking forward \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.39,0:02:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to expanding your ministry \Nin one of these areas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.59,0:02:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage you to do so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be assured \Nthat you will receive much fulfillment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.36,0:02:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and many blessings from Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there are others \Nwho are watching this program\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who may feel discouraged \Nbecause their circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.64,0:02:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,may seem to limit \Ntheir being as involved as they would like. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.28,0:02:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some of these circumstances? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.88,0:02:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These may include our age, our health, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.89,0:02:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,our economic situation, \Nor our physical limitations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For some of us, \Nperhaps our upbringing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.89,0:03:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or past errors \Nwe have made in our life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,may cause us to feel \Nthat we are limited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.20,0:03:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what we can do \Nfor Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know well, \Nfocusing on our limitations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.47,0:03:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,can affect our joy, \Ncausing discouragement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.58,0:03:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many examples \Nin the Scriptures of men and women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who had circumstances \Nbeyond their control \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that seemed to limit how much \Nthey could do for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Others had to deal with the effects \Nof their upbringing and family life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or with serious errors they made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they allow themselves to be limited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by their circumstances or their past? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah feel about them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah feel about us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what we are going to discuss \Nin this month’s broadcast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.21,0:03:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which has the theme \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.61,0:03:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Defined by Your Circumstances?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.62,0:03:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start by looking at some \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.79,0:04:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who could have let \Ntheir circumstances limit them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider first the example \Nof Joseph in the book of Genesis. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.13,0:04:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Joseph faced injustice at its worst. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,His situation was especially hurtful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.14,0:04:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,since it was initially brought on by those \Nwho should have been closest to him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.87,0:04:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—his family! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,As a slave in Egypt \Nand later as a prisoner, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.98,0:04:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph was indeed limited \Nin what he could do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How might Joseph have reacted? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.85,0:04:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, \NJoseph could have become so preoccupied \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.85,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with what he could not do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that he lost sight of what he could do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.99,0:04:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Joseph let his circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,paralyze his life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He chose to make \Nthe best of his situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \Nnote what Joseph did \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,while serving as a slave \Nin Potiphar’s house \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if we turn together \Nto Genesis 39:4: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“Joseph kept finding favor in his eyes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.58,0:05:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he became his personal attendant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“So he appointed him over his house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and he put him \Nin charge of all that was his.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph worked diligently \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,within the limitations \Nof his circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.16,0:05:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He took a similar approach while in prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.43,0:05:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph focused on what he could do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,despite suffering the effects of injustice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.31,0:05:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As a second example, \Nconsider Hezekiah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah is one \Nwho might easily have felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was defined by his upbringing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the terrible example \Nthat was set by his father, Ahaz, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.65,0:05:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded in 2 Kings chapter 16. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.72,0:05:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Kings chapter 16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice what verse 3 says about Ahaz: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Instead, he walked in the way \Nof the kings of Israel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he even made his own son \Npass through the fire, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:05:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“following the detestable practices \Nof the nations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.61,0:06:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah had driven out \Nfrom before the Israelites.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah’s father did detestable things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in opposition to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hezekiah showed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.55,0:06:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was not the helpless victim \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.66,0:06:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of a poor parental example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.69,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, turn in your Bibles \Nto 2 Kings chapter 18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.56,0:06:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice verse 3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what it says about Hezekiah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“He kept doing what was right\Nin Jehovah’s eyes,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.14,0:06:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just as David his forefather\Nhad done.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 5 says of Hezekiah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.65,0:06:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“There was no one like him \Namong all the kings of Judah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He became fully involved in true worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Verses 6 and 7 say that Hezekiah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘held fast to Jehovah, \Nand Jehovah proved to be with him.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How encouraging \NHezekiah’s example is for us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.13,0:06:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We can choose to be loyal to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.57,0:07:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and do much in our worship of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.80,0:07:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we did not grow up in a family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.54,0:07:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that served Jehovah fully. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.54,0:07:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not helpless victims \Nof our environment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah’s example \Nreassures us that our past \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.95,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,does not have to control our future.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a third example, \Nconsider the apostle Paul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not let his own past mistakes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.73,0:07:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,involving religious prejudice and violence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,stop him from giving his all to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Paul feel about his past? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s read together \Nat 1 Corinthians 15:9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I am the least of the apostles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.25,0:07:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I am not worthy \Nof being called an apostle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.45,0:07:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because I persecuted \Nthe congregation of God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.49,0:07:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am the least of the apostles.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.46,0:07:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, when writing to the Ephesians \Nas recorded at Ephesians 3:8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he calls himself \N“less than the least of all holy ones.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, at 1 Timothy 1:15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.43,0:08:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he now calls himself \Nthe “foremost” of all sinners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.44,0:08:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, \NPaul’s prior treatment of the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,weighed heavily upon him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Could Paul have reasoned \Nthat he was damaged? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Could he have reasoned that his past \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,limited what he could do for Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.92,0:08:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have, \Nbut Paul did not do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.26,0:08:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He poured himself out \Nfor the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.13,0:08:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Paul was privileged to write \Nmore books and letters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.30,0:08:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Christian Greek Scriptures \Nthan anyone else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.83,0:08:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He demonstrated \Nan outstanding zeal for the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul did not let his conduct in the past \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,dictate what he could do for Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are many other examples as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.35,0:08:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nare we in a difficult economic situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The account in 2 Corinthians chapter 8\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.55,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us about the Macedonians.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says that they were in deep poverty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.09,0:09:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet they begged to have a financial share\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.03,0:09:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the relief work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we older in years? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We may think of Anna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The account at Luke 2:36-38\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.80,0:09:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us that she was 84 years old \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.74,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that her husband had died\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,after just seven years of marriage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.18,0:09:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, \N“she was never missing from the temple.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.55,0:09:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She rendered\N‘sacred service day and night.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons do we learn \Nfrom these accounts? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.29,0:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dear brothers and sisters\Nin Bible times were just like us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Many were in circumstances\Nthat they would not have chosen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.10,0:09:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet,\Nthey did not let their circumstances\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or their past define them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They joyfully did what they could \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.21,0:09:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,within the limits of their situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.91,0:09:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are just a few examples. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many others in the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:10:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not make it a personal study project \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to research faithful ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who were in circumstances \Nsimilar to yours? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they stay involved \Nin Jehovah’s work? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.56,0:10:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We are sure \Nthat you will be greatly encouraged.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.03,0:10:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \Nlet’s look at an example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.60,0:10:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of how you might do this \Nwith a familiar Bible character. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.37,0:10:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.54,0:10:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother and two sisters \Nuse their personal study time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.74,0:10:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn about Jonah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.05,0:10:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, as we know, \NJonah was discouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.85,0:10:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by events beyond his control; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.42,0:10:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at other times it was \Nbecause of his own failings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.89,0:10:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Jonah’s experience relate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.39,0:10:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to what they are feeling? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do the lessons \NJonah learned help them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.30,0:10:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to not remain trapped \Nin their circumstances?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.17,0:10:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But John, there’s still plenty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.54,0:11:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do \Nin the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.54,0:11:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, that sounds good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m no longer \Na ministerial servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I let my zeal \Nfor the ministry cool off? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what the brothers \Nmust think of me now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.26,0:11:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good morning. \NMy name is Jane. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.37,0:11:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad, thanks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you may not be interested, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have this tract \NI’d like to leave with you . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“You may not be interested?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.27,0:11:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.08,0:11:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my best presentation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but it didn’t seem like she wanted \Nto talk more anyway.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does that mean?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be manageable, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.06,0:11:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but long term, \Ngiven your other conditions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re looking at possibly \Nsome further tests . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.56,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Manageable? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Long term? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jehovah, \Nhow can I do this by myself?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course Jehovah values you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.69,0:12:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to think of someone in the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who may have felt like you do, \Nlike Jonah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.03,0:12:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Felt like I do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.38,0:12:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“What comes to your mind\Nwhen you think of Jonah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think of him \Nas a disobedient prophet?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.46,0:13:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Reluctant to obey Jehovah’s command, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jonah boarded a ship that carried him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.84,0:13:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,farther and farther away \Nfrom his assignment.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.35,0:13:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Did Jonah’s recent actions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.42,0:13:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“disqualify him \Nfrom ever again serving God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in an official capacity?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.39,0:13:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He sure could have thought so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.03,0:13:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.54,0:13:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“No, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah mercifully and lovingly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,renewed the prophet’s commission.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Jehovah didn’t see Jonah \Nas a total failure, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.93,0:14:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then what must he think of me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.27,0:14:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 16:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the way man sees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.41,0:14:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the way God sees.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jonah did not see Nineveh \Nas Jehovah did.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.47,0:14:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with all that they were doing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.64,0:14:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how could he view them any differently? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:14:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But the account says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.01,0:15:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘When God saw they had turned back \Nfrom their evil ways, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‘he reconsidered the calamity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.49,0:15:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he did not bring it.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.12,0:15:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Despite the people’s badness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah cared about them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“He values human life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.46,0:15:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the potential \Nthat each individual has \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for repenting and learning \Nto do what is right.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course that’s true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn’t Jonah see that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.85,0:15:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But am I seeing people\Nthe way Jehovah does?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.05,0:15:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I assuming they won’t listen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.29,0:15:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then not giving my best? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.06,0:15:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I know \Nhow a person will respond? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.70,0:15:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jonah learned to be merciful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.91,0:16:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 5:7 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are the merciful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.25,0:16:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,since they will be shown mercy.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jonah prayed to Jehovah his God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the belly of the fish, and he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.89,0:16:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Out of my distress \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I called out to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and he answered me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.20,0:16:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Out of the depths of the Grave \NI cried for help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard my voice.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.24,0:16:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,God heard Jonah and delivered him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can’t expect a miracle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.22,0:16:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then my prayer came in to you, \Ninto your holy temple.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.96,0:16:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“My prayer.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“My prayer came in to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:16:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah didn’t know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.10,0:17:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if Jehovah would rescue him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.14,0:17:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but he prayed in faith \Nthat Jehovah cared.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.74,0:17:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as for me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the voice of thanksgiving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.78,0:17:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will sacrifice to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.61,0:17:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“What I have vowed, I will pay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.92,0:17:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvation is from Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.96,0:17:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I still can, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.93,0:17:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll keep sacrificing to God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.77,0:17:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvation is from Jehovah!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Like those in our video, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,do you sometimes feel as Jonah did? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you apply the lessons \Nfrom Jonah’s account \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.02,0:17:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to better see God’s mercy \Nin your life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:17:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A personal failing \Ndiscouraged our brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.83,0:18:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But like Jonah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he realized Jehovah still valued him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.17,0:18:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our young sister \Nreinvigorated her ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.27,0:18:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,after meditating on the way Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.74,0:18:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,mercifully viewed the Ninevites. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.54,0:18:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And our sister was determined \Nto imitate Jonah’s faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.05,0:18:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that God hears our prayers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.35,0:18:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about circumstances beyond our control.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.35,0:18:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, however, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.49,0:18:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,our circumstances \Nare only perceived barriers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.36,0:18:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to doing more for Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, some may feel limited \Nby economic concerns\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.93,0:18:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if they reach out for special privileges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.10,0:18:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Netherlands, \Nmany brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.54,0:18:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,assisted with the construction \Nof the Swifterbant Assembly Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Some had to make adjustments \Nto be able to work on this project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.71,0:18:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, however, to their comments \Non the blessings they received  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.62,0:19:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what their goals are \Nnow that the project is completed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.56,0:19:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Netherlands, \Nthere was a need for a new, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.20,0:19:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,suitable Assembly Hall, \Nwhich could accommodate almost all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.20,0:19:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 300 congregations \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional building ground \Nwas acquired next to the existing hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.98,0:19:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that a second, \Ncompletely new hall could be constructed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 200 volunteers \Nworked on this project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.19,0:19:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What challenges did they face? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what blessings did they receive?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.10,0:19:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to sell our house \Nand close our business.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.50,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a step into the unknown.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.87,0:19:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to quit my job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.11,0:19:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exciting to step \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.11,0:19:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out of my comfort zone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and rely completely on Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.38,0:20:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is structured, organized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why things run smoothly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.18,0:20:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn’t come naturally to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We were invited to come \Nand work in the kitchen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.89,0:20:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I love to cook at home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really fond of it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What was my assignment? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.50,0:20:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing the dishes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.94,0:20:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Working on yourself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.31,0:20:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,your Christian personality, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.31,0:20:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and cooperating \Nwith your brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.05,0:20:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—that has everlasting value.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was wonderful training for the future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.89,0:20:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when we will be building together \Nin Paradise.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.76,0:20:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that everyone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifices something and becomes happier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No one regrets their decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.00,0:20:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That Jehovah takes into account \Nyour personal makeup, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that he is patient with us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.97,0:20:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve really learned how to work together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.77,0:21:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a theocratic arrangement \Nand still have fun.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.54,0:21:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can work on yourself all day long \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.28,0:21:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore be able to improve.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.12,0:21:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I really learned to study more \Nand to read the Bible more often.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.05,0:21:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we worked together so closely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.36,0:21:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you got to know each other very well \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.36,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I really started \Nto love and appreciate people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.83,0:21:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We really came to appreciate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.10,0:21:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that every brother and sister \Nhas this beautiful inner person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.68,0:21:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Visitors and contractors \Nwere always very surprised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.85,0:21:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that there were so many women \Nworking at the construction site.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.35,0:21:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s great working with sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.55,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a construction background, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.26,0:21:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and communication with men \Ncan be really up front. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.26,0:21:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn’t work with sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.39,0:21:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You just have to be calm, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.40,0:21:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,talk, and listen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to work on a lift platform, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.71,0:22:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was kind of a problem \Nbecause I’m afraid of heights. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.78,0:22:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers were so kind \Nto seal the sides up completely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.18,0:22:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I could not look down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.39,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fun working together \Non that lift platform. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We called it our little flat.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.39,0:22:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The atmosphere was amazing, \Nand we all had a great time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.50,0:22:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we work in the kitchen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Swifterbant School Facility\N—a real privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.31,0:22:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been trained \Nto cook during construction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.68,0:22:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but if needed,\NI’ll even do the dishes as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.18,0:22:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never work five days again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.45,0:22:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I work three days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.05,0:22:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and since July 1st, \NI started pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.02,0:22:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just great.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.69,0:22:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He was offered a job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.69,0:22:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He could even choose between two jobs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he works three days a week, \Nwhich always seemed impossible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.30,0:23:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, we were \Nin Swifterbant for one month only.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.14,0:23:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we went to Mozambique \Nfor three months.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.24,0:23:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then for five months \Nto Swifterbant again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then three months in South Africa.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel called and assigned us \Nto Congo (Kinshasa).\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.67,0:23:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All the volunteers who helped \Nto make a success of this project— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.04,0:23:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they had to give up a lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, \Nwe can enjoy this beautiful hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.38,0:23:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing to be here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.51,0:23:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s great to be encouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.45,0:23:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be strengthened for the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.95,0:23:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.42,0:24:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,every day we have \Naround 700 new brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.79,0:24:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That means every three days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.79,0:24:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we could fill a hall like this \Nwith new brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.70,0:24:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,These kinds of halls \Nare really needed worldwide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.87,0:24:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to provide education \Nto all those additional brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.67,0:24:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so faith-strengthening to be here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.47,0:24:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Words cannot express it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.91,0:24:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel so united, so warm, peaceful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.21,0:24:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so wonderful to be able \Nto serve Jehovah together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.20,0:24:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice a common thread \Nin the volunteers’ comments? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.20,0:24:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Any economic concerns they may have had \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.04,0:24:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,just faded into the background,\Ndidn’t they?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.54,0:24:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They reached out to help, \Nand in turn Jehovah helped them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.25,0:25:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the Assembly Hall project\Nwas finished at a lower cost\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and a year earlier than originally planned.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.42,0:25:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you note that after the project,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.76,0:25:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,some who previously felt\Nthey couldn’t pioneer\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.76,0:25:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,reduced their secular workdays \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.03,0:25:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and are now doing \Nwhat they thought was out of reach? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.46,0:25:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings us joy to see \Nso many making adjustments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.00,0:25:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and reaching out to do more \Nfor the organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.44,0:25:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and in turn they experience \Nsomething they’ll never forget.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.38,0:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nwe’ve considered examples of those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who did not let \Ntheir circumstances hinder them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.22,0:25:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from giving their all to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.55,0:25:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But another question is: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.02,0:25:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah \Nview his faithful servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.86,0:25:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,despite their limitations?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.20,0:25:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I’ve often thought \Nabout the example of John the Baptizer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.70,0:25:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know, he was arrested \Nshortly after Jesus started his ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.40,0:25:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,John could have felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.41,0:26:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was no longer of use \Nto Jehovah or the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.64,0:26:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, as recorded at Matthew 11:11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.55,0:26:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said about John: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.72,0:26:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Among those born of women, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.99,0:26:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there has not been raised up \Nanyone greater than John the Baptist.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.66,0:26:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s and Jesus’ view of John \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.89,0:26:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was not based \Non the man’s circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.49,0:26:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of being in prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.63,0:26:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Their view of John was based on\Nwho he was on the inside\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.70,0:26:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and on his relationship with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.47,0:26:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah did not focus on the limitations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.07,0:26:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In Jehovah’s eyes, \NJohn was great. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.34,0:26:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was still a faithful servant \Ndoing the best that he could, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.15,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was all that really mattered.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example \Nthat may come to your mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.25,0:26:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is that of King David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.29,0:26:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know, \NKing David committed serious sins. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.29,0:26:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, \NDavid repented for his sins, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.80,0:26:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no record\Nthat he repeated them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.70,0:27:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah view him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.57,0:27:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Jehovah see David as damaged, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.91,0:27:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,as a man who would always be\Nlimited in serving him?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.91,0:27:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Jehovah’s words \Ndirected to King Jeroboam \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.35,0:27:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Kings 14:8:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.58,0:27:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you have not become \Nlike my servant David, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.92,0:27:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“who kept my commandments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.92,0:27:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“and who walked after me \Nwith all his heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.79,0:27:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,doing only what was right in my eyes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.96,0:27:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah viewed David \Nas a special servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.83,0:27:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He says that he \N“kept my commandments.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.34,0:27:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He did \N“what was right in my eyes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.24,0:27:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Jehovah remembered.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.68,0:27:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How encouraging that is for us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.24,0:27:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If we have repented \Nof our past mistakes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.85,0:27:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and set matters straight \Nto the best of our circumstances, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.38,0:27:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we too can be assured \Nthat Jehovah loves us dearly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.42,0:27:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He appreciates whatever we can do \Nin our worship of him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.13,0:28:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the point? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.13,0:28:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, our past \Nor our present circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.20,0:28:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,do not define our value before Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.21,0:28:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Father loves us for who we are, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.44,0:28:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and he values our efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.44,0:28:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as we do the best \Nthat we can to serve him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.95,0:28:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think it is important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.02,0:28:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that we strive to see ourselves \Nas Jehovah does? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.79,0:28:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we can weaken, \Ndiscourage, or limit ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.66,0:28:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if we see ourselves only \Nin the framework of our circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.66,0:28:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,May we work hard not to do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.67,0:28:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Jehovah see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.07,0:28:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when he looks \Nat his faithful servants today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.81,0:28:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, turn, please, \Nto 1 Samuel 16:7. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.81,0:28:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the setting is \Nthat Samuel was about to go \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.38,0:28:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to anoint the next king of Israel; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.38,0:28:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he goes to the house of Jesse; \Nand Jesse lines up all of his sons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.82,0:29:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,except for David,\Nwho is still out in the field; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.32,0:29:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and Samuel walks in \Nand he sees Eliab. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.06,0:29:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And based on what he sees, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.56,0:29:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Samuel concludes that this surely must be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.30,0:29:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the next king of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.37,0:29:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, note what Jehovah saw. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.07,0:29:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please read with me 1 Samuel 16:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.07,0:29:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“But Jehovah said to Samuel: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.08,0:29:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do not pay attention \Nto his appearance and how tall he is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.62,0:29:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for I have rejected him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.92,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For the way man sees\Nis not the way God sees,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘because mere man sees\Nwhat appears to the eyes,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.19,0:29:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah sees into the heart.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.46,0:29:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the way Jehovah sees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.60,0:29:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He does not look \Nat our outward appearance and our abilities; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.60,0:29:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he sees into our hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.47,0:29:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees what we would be doing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.97,0:29:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if all of the limitations \Nwere lifted off of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.71,0:29:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, just the fact \Nthat we keep going, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.21,0:29:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that we keep putting \None foot in front of the other, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.51,0:30:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,endears us to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.68,0:30:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We understand the truth \Nof that statement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.52,0:30:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all may agree \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.52,0:30:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is how \NJehovah views his people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.53,0:30:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we may have \Na hard time convincing ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.23,0:30:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if this really applies to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.63,0:30:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever wondered: \N‘Does Jehovah really see me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.74,0:30:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Does he see what’s in my heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.84,0:30:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and value my desire to do more for him?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.41,0:30:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.41,0:30:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jehovah has already seen \Nwhat is in your heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.28,0:30:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.62,0:30:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you watching this program? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.82,0:30:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you care about spiritual things? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.66,0:30:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you, perhaps, \Nthe only one in your family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.59,0:30:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a dedicated, \Nbaptized servant of Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.53,0:30:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or why are you, perhaps, \Nthe only one at your place of employment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.10,0:30:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or the only one near where you live \Nwho’s serving Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.11,0:30:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because you are \Nso much more studious \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.71,0:31:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or smarter than everyone else? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.01,0:31:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.01,0:31:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Haggai 2:7 tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah \N“will shake all the nations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.39,0:31:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the precious things \Nof all the nations will come in.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.19,0:31:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,John 6:44 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.73,0:31:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘no man can come to Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.00,0:31:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,unless the Father draws him.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.60,0:31:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 31:3, Jehovah says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.00,0:31:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have loved you with an everlasting love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.74,0:31:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I have drawn you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, why are you serving Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.98,0:31:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah loves you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.98,0:31:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah drew you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.99,0:31:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As he was shaking the nations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.62,0:31:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he looked down into your heart \Nand he saw something very precious \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.26,0:31:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and he drew you to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.43,0:31:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, \N“I want to draw this person to my Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.00,0:31:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“I want to draw this person to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.30,0:31:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I love this person.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.73,0:32:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah drew you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.94,0:32:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not because you have\Nperfect circumstances,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.67,0:32:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of your heart\Nand because he loves you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.58,0:32:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He greatly appreciates \Nthat his servants give their best to him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.12,0:32:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do we know \Nthat Jehovah really sees each one of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.49,0:32:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter where we are? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.66,0:32:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider an example: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.69,0:32:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of refugees who faced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,severe hardships in their home countries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.70,0:32:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,have sought shelter in parts of Europe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.13,0:32:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch how Jehovah \Nhas lovingly assured them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.14,0:32:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that they’re not alone \Nby satisfying their spiritual thirst.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.11,0:32:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Greece!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.15,0:32:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We really feel that Jehovah is blessing us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.98,0:32:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,by opening a large door \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.99,0:32:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of opportunities to preach the good news \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.59,0:32:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to the many refugees \Nwho are streaming into the country.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.70,0:33:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, the brothers \Nimmediately informed us of the situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.60,0:33:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we directed the bodies of elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.27,0:33:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to concentrate on the harbors, \Nespecially in Chios.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.01,0:33:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers were willing to work in shifts\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.18,0:33:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—24 hours a day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.95,0:33:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The refugee shelters in our area \Nonly have families with children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.59,0:33:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and are located near a military airport.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.59,0:33:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever military planes flew overhead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.16,0:33:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the children would see and hear them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.16,0:33:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they would immediately run \Nand try to hide because they were afraid.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.03,0:33:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They sought protection \Nfrom the tragic conditions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.60,0:33:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they had experienced during warfare. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.80,0:33:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This impressed upon us \Nhow greatly they needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.94,0:33:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the comforting message of the good news, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.11,0:33:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we felt the urge to approach them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.18,0:33:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, \Nthe Service Department arranged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.22,0:33:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for four language classes \Nto be held for the brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.32,0:34:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to speak to people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.32,0:34:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in a language quite different from our own. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, we might think: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.86,0:34:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Will these people understand us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.96,0:34:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we be able to reach \Ntheir heart with these basic truths?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.53,0:34:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that helped me not to hesitate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.24,0:34:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to approach these people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.54,0:34:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the language barrier \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.27,0:34:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is what our teachers told us \Nin the language class: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.37,0:34:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go and talk to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.38,0:34:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Show them things from the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.11,0:34:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even if you don’t say things perfectly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.41,0:34:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they will understand you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.68,0:34:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,After we received permission \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.68,0:34:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from the branch office, \Nwe also printed thousands of tracts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.99,0:34:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,since we did not have enough. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.02,0:34:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole effort created \Nan atmosphere of enthusiasm.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.40,0:34:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m deeply moved when I see how lovingly\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.03,0:34:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah cares for these people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.77,0:34:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who have never had the opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.17,0:34:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear the Kingdom message \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.60,0:34:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives them a future and a hope.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.67,0:34:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exciting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.71,0:34:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for them to hear that we have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.71,0:34:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a Bible-based video in their language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.38,0:35:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We told them that the problems, calamities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.25,0:35:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the terrible war they had experienced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.65,0:35:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,were not punishment from God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.66,0:35:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but the result of the influence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.66,0:35:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan the Devil exercises \Nover this system of things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.23,0:35:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this provided \Na good answer to their question.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.37,0:35:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,On a return visit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.37,0:35:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,after two days, \Na refugee girl said something very touching: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.34,0:35:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now I understand why \Nwe have to go through all this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.04,0:35:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s very difficult, \Nbut it’s not God’s fault.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.04,0:35:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On another occasion, \NGardinia, a refugee woman \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.85,0:35:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who showed interest, told us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.85,0:35:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Since meeting you, \NI have a purpose in life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.05,0:35:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have a reason to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.05,0:35:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, I was just waiting to die.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.29,0:35:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A refugee approached \Nthe Arabic witnessing cart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.30,0:35:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we read Revelation 21:4 to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.00,0:35:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “Please, \Ncould you read that to me once again?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.74,0:35:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we read it a second time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.74,0:35:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He replied, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.61,0:35:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“May I have a Bible of my own?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.61,0:36:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we gave him a Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.28,0:36:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he said, \N“Would you please show me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.91,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the sentence you read in my Bible?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we marked the verse for him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.28,0:36:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the way back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.12,0:36:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to our home at about 11 o’clock at night, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.32,0:36:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on the same road, at a well-lit point, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.32,0:36:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that same refugee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.19,0:36:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on the sidewalk reading the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.16,0:36:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,About two and a half years ago, \NI met Moustafa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.33,0:36:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He attended the meetings \Nand made speedy progress. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.10,0:36:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Moustafa was baptized a few months \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.14,0:36:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,before the refugees started pouring in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.54,0:36:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not believe \Nthat this was a coincidence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.11,0:36:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He would say, \N“I want to speak about Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.51,0:36:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can’t do that \Nin the Greek language.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.68,0:36:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I can speak to people who are refugees\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.72,0:36:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—just as I am a refugee—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.82,0:36:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in my own language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.85,0:36:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a great opportunity for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.06,0:36:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I see that they listen \Nto the truth and are loving it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.36,0:36:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes my heart beat faster. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:36:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It touches my heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.50,0:37:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,By expanding my ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.50,0:37:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sharing in a form of service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.50,0:37:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that could even be described \Nas missionary work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.84,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,since I’m helping \Npeople hear about Jehovah  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the very first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m living what I have only read \Nabout in experiences.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.12,0:37:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Many were\N—perhaps for the first time—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.99,0:37:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,discovering new skills in themselves, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.59,0:37:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating how Jehovah \Nthrough his spirit can enable certain ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.99,0:37:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to cultivate qualities they didn’t realize \Nthey had to such an extent.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.43,0:37:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We are so grateful to Jehovah \Nfor opening a door \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.44,0:37:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,leading to such wonderful activity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.67,0:37:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us great joy, \Nand we praise him daily for this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.05,0:37:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time this report was prepared, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.52,0:37:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,over 100 Bible studies had been started. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.85,0:37:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One refugee told the brothers: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.12,0:37:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are the best thing \Nthat has happened to us here in Greece. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.12,0:37:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jehovah for meeting you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.96,0:38:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Another said: \N“We do not need material things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.03,0:38:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“We need hope, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.83,0:38:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are giving this \Nto us through the Bible.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.07,0:38:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In our program, we have been discussing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.54,0:38:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah values each one of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.64,0:38:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what our circumstances are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.04,0:38:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In some parts of the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.08,0:38:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters \Nare in deep poverty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and lack even the basic needs for life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.05,0:38:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But this does not diminish \NJehovah’s feelings for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.89,0:38:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He loves them dearly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.39,0:38:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In this next report, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.39,0:38:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,see what’s been done \Nto care for faithful brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.23,0:38:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Democratic Republic of Congo.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.61,0:38:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Maska Mahamba. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.98,0:38:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.98,0:38:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,However, my various illnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.98,0:38:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prevent me from giving \Nmy all in the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.79,0:39:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My first wife died, \Nand we had six children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.13,0:39:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was alone with the six children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.63,0:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I married Beatrice, \Nwho has five children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.97,0:39:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we are living in the last days \Nof this system, it is not easy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.54,0:39:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the example of Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.54,0:39:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who was passionate about preaching \Nthe message that he shared. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.91,0:39:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.55,0:39:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he took into account \Nthe suffering of the people of his time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.75,0:39:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He would take time to show kindness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.06,0:39:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage, and to heal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.76,0:39:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The branch sees where there is a need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.90,0:39:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then organizes a humanitarian mission.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.83,0:39:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I can use my medical skills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.60,0:39:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to help our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.07,0:39:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.28,0:39:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not just in writing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.61,0:39:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but in action.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.95,0:40:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a real joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.38,0:40:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to help these brothers who need us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.78,0:40:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in remote locations far from towns. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.52,0:40:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is always a pleasure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.12,0:40:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the two are the same; \Nboth eardrums are completely perforated.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.28,0:41:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we are here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.28,0:41:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the village of Walikale in the middle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.29,0:41:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the forest on the main road\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.32,0:41:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—well, the only road in the village. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.42,0:41:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It serves as our runway. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.76,0:41:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t bear to see anyone suffer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.33,0:41:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I use all my skills to try \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.50,0:41:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a solution.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.44,0:41:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What moves me to help the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.70,0:41:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is what Jesus said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.71,0:41:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that “there is more happiness in giving than\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.01,0:41:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . in receiving.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.01,0:41:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A long day\N—really very tiring—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.35,0:41:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the same time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.38,0:41:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there was an encouraging case: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.62,0:41:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Munyakaragwe, 68 years old, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.35,0:41:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,10 years in the regular pioneer service, \Nand he has 15 Bible studies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.46,0:41:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This brother came \Nfrom the territory on a motorcycle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.73,0:41:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It took him two and a half hours \Non a very rough road \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.67,0:41:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of an hour and a half \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.90,0:42:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because he has a paralyzed leg. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.64,0:42:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was able to go \Nback to his field service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.64,0:42:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,well, with some medication. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.54,0:42:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was really encouraging to see him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.71,0:42:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,getting on the motorcycle \Nwith a smile on his face.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.89,0:42:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These are mosquito nets for those in need, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.23,0:42:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s a big need here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.86,0:42:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we give them to each family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.20,0:42:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, to protect your baby, \None of the best things is for him  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.57,0:42:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to sleep under a mosquito net.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.41,0:42:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has done well because he has gone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.77,0:42:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,through you to provide us with care.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.84,0:42:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very grateful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.78,0:42:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank the many brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.25,0:42:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who have volunteered to serve us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.52,0:42:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank Jehovah because without him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.12,0:42:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,our identifying mark of unity wouldn’t exist.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.92,0:42:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You have helped me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.46,0:42:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I had this problem for two years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.46,0:43:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m so happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.79,0:43:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be able to hear at the meetings again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.40,0:43:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.87,0:43:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers are aware \Nthat they must thank Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.80,0:43:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and we ourselves are aware \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.80,0:43:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that all of this is possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.27,0:43:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to Jehovah’s holy spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.94,0:43:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and his organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.50,0:43:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How heartwarming!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.51,0:43:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those dear ones are not defined \Nby their circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.58,0:43:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They have been serving Jehovah \Nwhole-souled despite their challenges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.88,0:43:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re determined \Nto use the relief assistance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.55,0:43:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue worshipping him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.59,0:44:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, we discussed \Nthe examples of King David \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.56,0:44:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and the apostle Paul \Nand the mistakes they made.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.79,0:44:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps for us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.83,0:44:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,our past mistakes are keeping us \Nfrom moving forward. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.50,0:44:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the challenge for Jim Loyd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.64,0:44:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was raised in the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.04,0:44:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but did not progress to baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.44,0:44:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,By his teen years, \Nhe was getting into trouble. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.48,0:44:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As he describes it, \Nin his heart he had left Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.78,0:44:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,His later involvement \Nwith gangs and violence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.75,0:44:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,put him in a place \Nhe never expected to be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.95,0:44:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But you will be greatly encouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.66,0:44:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to see where he is now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.13,0:44:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that have happened to you, \Nyou can’t change\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.33,0:44:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—but your personality you can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.73,0:44:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We can change our personality \Nwith Jehovah’s help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.74,0:44:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I was 25, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.74,0:44:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was associating with notorious criminals.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.87,0:44:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I was a criminal too\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.41,0:44:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—just took a wrong turn and kept going.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.91,0:45:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I found myself a fugitive on the run. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.85,0:45:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sentenced to many years in prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.35,0:45:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,At 25, I felt like it might as well \Nhave been a life sentence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.49,0:45:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Isolation and lockdown \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.03,0:45:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was a very lonely place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.16,0:45:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought, \N‘How did I get here?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.50,0:45:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a happier time in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.27,0:45:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom would take us to meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.94,0:45:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the Theocratic Ministry School. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.85,0:45:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All the friends were so loving. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.88,0:45:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom sent me subscriptions \Nto The Watchtower and Awake! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.89,0:45:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a box under my bunk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.99,0:45:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’d toss them in there\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.43,0:45:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—never opened them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.30,0:45:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I must have had a years’ worth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.26,0:45:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I never told her: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.90,0:45:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Stop sending them, Mom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.13,0:45:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not reading them.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.97,0:45:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out through my mom\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.97,0:46:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that my dad had died. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.98,0:46:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt that I broke his heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.25,0:46:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I pulled out the box from under my bunk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.82,0:46:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on top was a book,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.66,0:46:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Truth That Leads to Eternal Life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.23,0:46:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that moment, I knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.43,0:46:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah hadn’t forgotten me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.30,0:46:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered that book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.60,0:46:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered that book when I was a boy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.31,0:46:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I placed that book out in service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.48,0:46:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I opened it up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.01,0:46:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the theme scripture \Nfor that publication \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.78,0:46:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was Revelation 21:3, 4: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.49,0:46:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“The tent of God is with mankind.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.42,0:46:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I read it that night the whole night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.06,0:46:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I read the whole book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.33,0:46:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that little bell went off. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.79,0:46:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t deny that this was the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.93,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what was I going to do about it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.17,0:47:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after that, I got transferred, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.74,0:47:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so I called my mom and told her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.30,0:47:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was funny; she asked, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.94,0:47:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you think there are\Nany Jehovah’s Witnesses\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.81,0:47:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that go up there?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.54,0:47:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her: “I don’t think so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.18,0:47:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s way up in the mountains. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.28,0:47:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think they go up there; \Nit’s a little fire camp.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.05,0:47:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t a spiritual person yet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.22,0:47:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All the magazines and books \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.72,0:47:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,went back into the box \Nand back under my bunk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.63,0:47:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d only been there five minutes,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.03,0:47:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and a guard came in and said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.33,0:47:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are you a Jehovah’s Witness?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.87,0:47:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.54,0:47:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told him, “I studied with, \Nbeen studying with Jehovah’s Witnesses.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.91,0:47:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said: \N“Oh, good. Follow me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.38,0:47:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I followed him, \Nand he took me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.55,0:47:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and introduced me to a brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.32,0:47:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who had been coming up \Nthere regularly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.55,0:47:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the Bible \Nwith inmates there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.59,0:47:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.86,0:47:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment that once again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.99,0:48:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah had not forgotten me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.16,0:48:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That brother faithfully came up there\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.90,0:48:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next two years \Nevery Friday night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.71,0:48:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought that it’d be \Na good idea to have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.34,0:48:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a Theocratic Ministry School, \Nso he got it approved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.74,0:48:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He would do the number one talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.75,0:48:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other brother \Nthat would come with him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.75,0:48:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,would do the highlights,\Nand then the three of us inmates\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.65,0:48:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,would do the other parts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.42,0:48:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was giving a talk every week.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.09,0:48:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And he started making \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.09,0:48:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,tape recordings of the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.63,0:48:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d listen to them over and over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.03,0:48:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,until the next week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.33,0:48:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that if I was going \Nto return to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.73,0:48:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to make some adjustments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.74,0:48:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help\N—I leaned on him more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.37,0:48:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,relied on his strength more—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.28,0:48:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it was then that I really felt \Nthat I could do this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.08,0:48:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The beard became a goatee, \Nand then it just became a mustache. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.45,0:48:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No drugs, no alcohol, no smoking, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.72,0:49:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I cleaned up my language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.89,0:49:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I finally got released, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.79,0:49:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,got a job as an electrician, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.96,0:49:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and was able to get my own place\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.33,0:49:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and started going to meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.64,0:49:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was listening to the Watchtower, \Nand different ones were commenting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.74,0:49:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh, that’s his wife’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.74,0:49:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—one of the brothers \Nwho came up to visit me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.78,0:49:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept looking to see, \Nso I could finally put a face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.78,0:49:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to the voices\Nthat I’d been listening to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.69,0:49:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I let Jehovah mold me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.32,0:49:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,into something good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.29,0:49:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many blessings \Nsince dedicating my life to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.16,0:49:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been an elder for ten years now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.03,0:49:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my sons came into the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.04,0:49:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I met my wonderful wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.37,0:49:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s helped me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.37,0:49:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to grow spiritually \Nand to love Jehovah even more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.71,0:50:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I kept praying for and he’s blessed\Nme with is to forgive myself\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.58,0:50:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—to have a clean conscience \Nand freeness of speech. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.15,0:50:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he’s done that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.86,0:50:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jim shares the same joy as so many others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.96,0:50:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who return to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.13,0:50:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The feelings common \Nin such real-life experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.54,0:50:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are what we’ll see depicted \Nin our music video. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.81,0:50:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s called I Can Get Back Up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.67,0:50:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It is especially touching \Nfor those of us who have stumbled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.11,0:50:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but need encouragement \Nto move ahead with Jehovah’s help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.23,0:51:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This loneliness I feel inside \Nis hard to bear.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.81,0:51:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, I can see where I went wrong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.58,0:51:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling so downhearted, \NI need strength to carry on.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.12,0:51:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m yearning to be back where I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.66,0:51:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember things you taught me\N—things I still recall—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.04,0:51:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The precious truths found \Nin your Holy Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.35,0:51:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That even if I stumble, even if I fall,\NI can get back up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.83,0:52:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the ones who care for me,\NWho showed their love before,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.47,0:52:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who love Jehovah from the heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.08,0:52:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your word is like a lamp \Nthat lights the way that leads me back.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.42,0:52:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The road to life is where I want to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.83,0:52:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ev’rywhere I go, ev’rything I see, \Nreminds me of the truth:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.70,0:52:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is drawing near.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.04,0:52:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah, Father, \Nplease hear my prayer tonight\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.39,0:53:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And help me now, \NI’m in my time of need.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.26,0:53:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that when I stumble \Nso many times,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.90,0:53:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get back up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.28,0:53:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah understands; \Nsometimes I need a helping hand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.23,0:53:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that I am weak \Nand sees what others cannot see.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.80,0:53:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s looking for the best in me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.67,0:53:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m going to the hall tonight \Nto feel the love I lost,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.52,0:54:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to where I know I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.59,0:54:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if I stumble, \Neven if I fall, I will get back up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.02,0:54:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get back up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.59,0:54:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful reminder \Nthat if we stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.86,0:54:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we can get back up! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.40,0:54:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Having seen the examples \Nthroughout the program,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.53,0:54:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can you confidently answer \Nthe question of our theme, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.17,0:54:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Defined by Your Circumstances?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.87,0:54:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.88,0:55:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, \Nnot the way man sees is the way God sees\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.51,0:55:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah sees what the heart is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.12,0:55:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,May we work hard\Nto see ourselves as Jehovah does\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.39,0:55:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and be determined to never give up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.96,0:55:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,May we never forget that it is\Nthe privilege of bearing Jehovah’s name,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.03,0:55:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,having a relationship with him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.13,0:55:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and our love for Jehovah that defines us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.43,0:55:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is happy \Nif we give the best that we can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.11,0:55:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So may we do our part\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.31,0:55:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by not limiting ourselves \Ndue to our circumstances,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.85,0:55:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but always look for ways \Nto give our best to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.62,0:55:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You beautiful older ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.08,0:55:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,even those with severe health problems, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.29,0:55:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can do much to help \Nin the great work that’s taking place today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.56,0:55:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may wonder \Nwhat can you do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.86,0:55:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pray for your brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.99,0:55:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We need your prayers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.46,0:55:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.10,0:55:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for those who are taking the lead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.97,0:55:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for the elders in your congregations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.54,0:55:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for those who \Nare going through difficult times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.07,0:56:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do such prayers help \Nthe work of the organization? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.54,0:56:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.54,0:56:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,James 5:16 tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.51,0:56:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘a righteous person’s supplication \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.18,0:56:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,has a powerful effect.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.72,0:56:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter who we are \Nand whatever our situation in life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.29,0:56:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,may we find joy \Nin giving what we can for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.30,0:56:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And may each one of us \Nrejoice at the privilege we have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.33,0:56:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of being part of what Jehovah \Nis accomplishing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.94,0:56:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in these last days.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.71,0:56:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we share that privilege \Nwith our worldwide brotherhood\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.14,0:56:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—a part of which we enjoy \Nseeing each month. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.28,0:56:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude this program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.45,0:56:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we visit with our brothers \Nand sisters in Togo.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.75,0:56:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Located in western Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.29,0:56:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Togo enjoys \Na very pleasant climate year-round. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.16,0:56:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The southern coast contains \Nextensive lagoons with sandy beaches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.40,0:57:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,while farther north are \Nrolling forested hills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.07,0:57:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and yellow tinges of savanna land. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.84,0:57:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Togo may be one \Nof the smaller countries in Africa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.48,0:57:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, it is sending up a great shout \Nof praise to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.61,0:57:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the town of Kpalimé, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.65,0:57:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,there are 577 of our brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.59,0:57:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,56 of whom are pioneers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.99,0:57:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kpalimé is located \Non a scenic woodland plateau. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.73,0:57:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Steep hillsides can sometimes \Nmake service a challenge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.76,0:57:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but not a deterrent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.13,0:57:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our faithful brothers and sisters \Nnot only meet this challenge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.00,0:57:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but are very zealous \Nin carrying out their ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.01,0:57:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They diligently search out all persons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.88,0:57:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter where they are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.88,0:57:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And many honesthearted ones are listening \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.95,0:57:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to the good news from God’s Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.12,0:57:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The first congregation in Kpalimé \Nwas formed in 1961. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.99,0:57:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there are seven \Nin this small town alone! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.86,0:58:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kingdom Halls \Nare very well cared for by the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.40,0:58:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the newest Kingdom Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.50,0:58:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Kpalimé-Nogo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.23,0:58:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just dedicated \Nin December 2016. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.80,0:58:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is their Assembly Hall, \Nconstructed in 2008. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.88,0:58:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All 577 send you \Ntheir love and greetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.05,0:58:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we, in turn, \Nsend them our love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.08,0:58:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray for Jehovah’s strength and blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.59,0:58:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to be upon each and every one of them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.82,0:58:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.66,0:58:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!\N
